On Wednesday, May 12, 2004, at 04:13PM, Paul Manning <paulmanning97(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

>I can't find the thermostat.

It's under the #1/#2 cylinders. Here are all the parts:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Maintenance2/220-ThermostatHardware.jpg

>I'd like to be sure that the PO was thorough in his/her demolition of
>the cooling system before I start buying parts. Can I check for the
>existence of flaps without pulling the fan housing?

There is a bar across the top of the engine just behind the fan shroud. If the flaps are there you should feel the resistance as you rotate the bar.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Engine2/05-AirflapSpring.jpg
http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Engine2/06-AsymmetricFlaps.jpg

>In the archives,
>Steve Bartnik said that the fan housing can be removed without pulling
>the engine. Has anyone done this? Is it any worse/easier than pulling
>the ALT without pulling the engine?

The shroud is pretty heavy and lopsided with the alternator still attached. I'd remove that first.

